text: Natalia Gordienko (born 11 December 1987) is a Moldovan singer. She is best known internationally for representing Moldova at the Eurovision Song Contest 2021 with the song "Sugar", which finished 13th place in the final. She has competed in various other competitions. Gordienko had previously represented Moldova at Eurovision in 2006 alongside Arsenium and Connect-R. She was due to represent Moldova at Eurovision 2020 but it was cancelled. == Awards == In 2008, Gordienko received honorary title of ″Emeritus Artist″ of Moldova. == Sources == Category:1987 births Category:Living people Category:Moldovan singers Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants
